  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine Arabic rice, chicken breast, coconut oil, salt, black pepper, and Japanese chili flakes.",
    "Mix well until the chicken is evenly coated with the spice blend.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking sheet and roast in the preheated oven for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the baking sheet from the oven and let it cool slightly.",
    "Using a mortar and pestle, pound the roasted rice mixture into a fine crumb.",
    "Add the roasted sesame seeds and chopped scallions to the pounded rice mixture and mix well.",
    "Divide the rice mixture into 6 equal portions and shape each portion into a triangular onigiri shape using the molds.",
    "Brush the tops of the onigiri with sesame oil and serve immediately."
  ],
